Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and half of the @Peri Peri seasoning{1}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Trim the @green beans{150} then chop into thirds. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). In a #medium sized bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{25} with the remaining Peri Peri seasoning and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over high heat. When hot add the beans, a splash of water and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir fry until the beans are tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic to the pan, reduce the heat and stir and continue to cook for ~{1%minute}. Transfer the beans to a #bowl{}, cover with #tin foil{} and set aside. Keep the frying pan!

Add the @mayonnaise{1} to a medium size bowl. Pat the @cod fillets{2} dry with some #kitchen roll{} and season the fish with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then add to the mayonnaise bowl. Coat the fish all over with mayonnaise. Place the fish into the Peri Peri Breadcrumbs one piece at a time and turn the fish to coat in the breadcrumbs.

> Make sure the fish is evenly coated.

When the potatoes have 10 mins left in the oven, wipe out the frying pan, add a glug of @oil{} and pop onto a medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, add the fish and fry until golden and crispy, ~{4-5%minutes} on each side.

> The fish is cooked when it is opaque in the middle.

Share the Peri Peri wedges between your plates. Serve the fish along side followed by the beans. Enjoy!